<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,940]" box="[189,1328,806,833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,806,832]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet refers to Mt. Nanhutashan, where the new species was discovered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,504,842,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Habitat and distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. D. Yang &amp; S. H. Lin" authorityYear="2014" box="[532,896,842,868]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Cololejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="nanhutashanensis">
<emphasis box="[532,896,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Cololejeunea nanhutashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an epiphyte found in altimontane forest. It grows on tree trunk of 
<taxonomicName box="[403,608,879,904]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[403,608,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Pinus taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in environment with filtered light and is currently known only from Mt. Nanhutashan, 
<collectingRegion box="[296,403,914,940]" country="Taiwan" name="Taichung" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Taichung</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[413,499,914,940]" name="Taiwan" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
